FBIS4-24278 "drafr124_d_94015" FBIS-AFR-94-124 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Mozambique Government Needs $950 Million To Repair Roads Government Needs $950 Million To Repair Roads MB2406185194 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 1030 GMT 24 Jun 94 MB2406185194 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network Portuguese BFN [Text] Mozambique needs $950 million to repair roads over a five-year period. Construction and Water Minister Joao Salomao said the money will be used to rehabilitate about 29,000 km of the national road network. The minister also said that about 80 percent of the budget will be used for repair work, opening of new roads, and regular road maintenance.
